## Log

2026-07-15  Scaffolded. No work started.

2026-07-15  source wip. Hunting the primary: a published switching order or clearance procedure that
            gives a circuit AND its own stated correct sequence, or that states the ORDERING RULES in
            its own words (a stated rule is as checkable as a stated answer). Two independent workers
            on the same target on purpose (pattern #12): agreement is evidence, disagreement is a
            finding, and duplication is the only reason 02's wrong equations ever surfaced.
            Unusually for this repo, the promising literature here is PUBLIC DOMAIN: OSHA 1910.147 and
            1910.269, DOE handbooks, Reclamation FIST, Army/NAVFAC, BPA/WAPA/TVA switching manuals.
            NFPA 70E and IEEE 3007.x are gated and copyrighted: cite by number, never use content.

            🔴 THE PLAN AND THE HAND OFF ARE BOTH WRONG ABOUT WHAT THIS PROJECT COSTS, and the error is
            worth keeping rather than quietly fixing. The plan sells the interlock: "07 plans switching
            orders on 01's one line." The hand off went further and predicted 07 was MISPRICED at 7th,
            "01's engine plus an ordering constraint... probably the cheapest remaining build."
            CHECKED IT INSTEAD OF INHERITING IT. 01's model has ELEVEN node types: ats, bus, bypass,
            generator, load, pdu, rack_ats, sts, tie, ups, utility. THERE IS NO BREAKER AND NO SWITCH
            IN ANY OF THEM. 01/build/topologies.js says so on purpose: "Breakers ... are folded into
            the edges rather than made into nodes ... A breaker level model would be a different and
            larger piece of work."
            A SWITCHING ORDER IS A SEQUENCE OF OPERATIONS ON BREAKERS AND SWITCHES. 01 removes NODES
            (named equipment) and has no operable devices at all, so the one thing 07 exists to compute
            is the one thing 01 cannot express. 07 needs a device level model. That is not a blocker,
            it is a COST, and it was hidden inside a sentence that sounded like reuse.
            WHAT SURVIVES: the hand off's OTHER argument for 07 is untouched and is the strong one.
            This is the app where Keaton has real authority (LOTO certified, recertified every 6
            months, 4 years in a live fab). That never depended on reusing 01.
            Lesson, same shape as this repo's others: AN INTERLOCK CLAIMED IN A PLAN IS A HYPOTHESIS.
            Open the other project's model and look before you price the build on it.

2026-07-15  source DONE. Primary: BPA Operating Bulletin No. 2 / Accident Prevention Rule S-6,
            "Switching and Clearance Procedure", Oct 1 2025, 86 pp, fetched from bpa.gov.
            🟢 THIS IS THE BEST SOURCE IN THE REPO, on both axes at once, and it is worth naming why
            rather than just celebrating. 01's WP75 and 02's GE 850 are both FREE BUT COPYRIGHTED, and
            02's was read at a DISTRIBUTOR because GE's own copy is login walled. This one is read at
            the PUBLISHER (curl, 200, no cross host redirect, BPA employee named as author in the
            metadata, Word as creator ⇒ an original, not a re render) AND it is PUBLIC DOMAIN (federal
            agency work, 17 USC 105). 07 is the first project that verifies against a document nobody
            owns, fetched from the people who wrote it.
            THE LICENCE WAS CHECKED, NOT ASSUMED, because 02 taught that A DOCUMENT'S LICENCE IS NOT
            UNIFORM (TM 5-811-14 is public domain EXCEPT the asterisked paragraph reprinting IEEE 242,
            which was the one paragraph 02 wanted). Searched all 86 pages for reprinted / permission /
            copyright / ©: ELEVEN hits, ALL of them "permission" in the operational sense (permission
            from the Dispatcher). Zero reprint notices. The licence here really is uniform.

            WHAT IT PUBLISHES. A STATED RULE and its OWN WORKED EXAMPLE OF THAT RULE.
            Rule, section IV.4.C, page label P-8, PDF p.12, verbatim: "PCB(s) shall be checked open
            before operating isolating devices." A flat imperative. No arithmetic, no tolerance, no
            convention: a sequence either honors it or it does not. THAT IS THE GATE.
            Worked example, section X.2 Example 1, page label P-45, PDF p.49: the Central-East Columbia
            No. 3 230 kV line is de-energized "by opening PCBs A-10 and A-3 by supervisory control",
            and only THEN are the isolating disconnects operated and tagged. The document applies its
            own rule to a named circuit with named devices. Same shape as 02's manual agreeing with
            itself three ways.
            The illustration is a DEVICE LEVEL one line, rendered at 3x and read as an image rather
            than inferred from the text layer: PCB A-10 with a disconnect either side + ground switch
            7233 at Central; PCB A-3 with a disconnect either side + ground switch 7243 at East
            Columbia. ~10 operable devices, 2 terminals. That is what 07 encodes.
            SECOND RULE, different publisher: 29 CFR 1910.269(n)(6), read at govinfo.gov. Attach the
            GROUND END FIRST then the line end; remove the LINE END FIRST then the ground end. The
            regulation states BOTH halves rather than saying "reverse", so both can be asserted.

            METHOD: TWO WORKERS, OPPOSITE INSTRUCTIONS, SAME ANSWER. One was told to start at OSHA,
            the other told explicitly NOT to and to start at utility switching manuals. They converged
            on the same document, same rule, same page, same worked example, and both independently
            found the same corroborator (Snohomish County PUD). Two different search paths landing on
            one document is evidence ABOUT THE DOCUMENT; one worker finding it twice would not be.
            Then everything the verify phase rests on was RE READ AT THE PUBLISHER by me, because a
            worker's honest grade is a warning and not a fix. Both workers' quotes and page labels
            survived exactly. Worker A's gaps section is the best this project has produced: it graded
            its own PyMuPDF extractions TRACED and its WebFetch-pipeline reads only READ IN FULL, and
            it flagged an unattributed cache artifact and REFUSED to rely on it.

            🔴 THE CRUX FOR THE BUILD, from the gaps: BPA NEVER PRINTS A FILLED IN SWITCHING ORDER.
            86 pages, no numbered "Step 1 / Step 2" order form filled in anywhere. Both workers found
            this independently. So VERIFY ASSERTS THE RULE against a generated sequence, plus the prose
            example's stated device order. IT CANNOT DIFF AGAINST A PUBLISHED STEP LIST, because no
            step list is published. Do not let a future session claim otherwise.
            Real negative finding, from reading both IN FULL: Reclamation FIST 1-1 and 1-2 contain NO
            filled in worked switching order either. They reference an SPF form that carries the device
            sequence and only ever show it blank.

            TOOLING, worth keeping: WebFetch's summarizer REFUSED to quote public domain CFR verbatim
            (citing a copyright policy that does not apply to federal regulations) and misreported the
            FIST PDFs as corrupted when they are normal text layer PDFs. curl + PyMuPDF solved both.
            And the CFR text layer interleaves the PRINTER'S PAGE FURNITURE INTO THE MIDDLE OF A
            SENTENCE ("...before he or she VerDate Sep<11>2014 ... Jkt 262121 ... removes the ground-end
            connection"), and hyphenates across line breaks ("em- ployees") so a literal search for the
            paragraph heading finds NOTHING and a careless reader concludes the paragraph is absent.
            Same family as 02's flattened fraction bar: THE TEXT LAYER IS NOT THE DOCUMENT.

            NEXT: learn/build. Remember the interlock finding above — 01 has no breakers, so 07 traces
            its OWN device level topology from the Example 1 illustration. That is the cost the plan
            and the hand off both hid inside the word "reuse".
